language Essence 1.3

$ Social Golfers Problem — Formulation 2: Sequence of Partitions
$
$ Domain:  sequence (size w) of partition (regular, numParts g, partSize s) from Golfers
$
$ Information carried by the domain:
$   - There are exactly w weeks (sequence size w)
$   - Each week is a partition of all golfers into groups
$   - Each partition has exactly g groups, each of size s (regular)
$   - Disjointness and full coverage: partition semantics
$   - Weeks are ordered (sequence introduces positional indexing)
$
$ Explicit constraints needed:
$   - Pairing constraint
$
$ Compared to Formulation 1 (set of partitions):
$   - Weeks now have an order (week 1, week 2, ...), introducing potential
$     week-ordering symmetry that was absent in the set formulation.
$   - The partition domain still carries all within-week structure.

given w, g, s : int(1..)

letting nGolfers be g * s
letting Golfers be new type of size nGolfers

find sched : sequence (size w) of partition (regular, numParts g, partSize s) from Golfers

$ Pairing constraint: no two golfers share a group more than once across weeks
such that
    forAll p1 : Golfers .
        forAll p2 : Golfers .
            p1 != p2 ->
            (sum i : int(1..w) .
                sum part in parts(sched(i)) .
                    toInt(p1 in part /\ p2 in part)
            ) <= 1
